NOTE: CINDY LOU AND NICHOLAS ARE A BONDED PAIR AND MUST BE ADOPTED TOGETHER.

CINDY LOU is a loving, 1-year-old, 22-pound (very underweight), Boxer mix. This young dog came to AA, the casualty of a cruelty case. She arrived with her companion Nicholas. Both dogs had been left outside in the freezing cold temperatures to starve. When the animal control officer went to the residence to remove the pair, he found Nicholas curled up around Cindy Lou trying to keep her warm. They are both very sweet, lovable young dogs who have suffered greatly at the hands of heartless, cruel individuals. Better photos and more information on the way. Link to NICHOLAS' Bio: https://www.petfinder.com/dog/nicholas-50355498/nj/lambertville/animal-alliance-nj290/ WHAT'S NEXT? If you would like to meet, foster or adopt this pet, please fill out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - simply copy and paste the link into your browser. EASY PEASY! Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you guys to meet! It'll be kind of like a blind date! *** This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives. Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. BY APPOINTMENT ONLY: Meetings at our Adoption Center are by appointment only (no walk-ins). An online adoption application is required and must be approved prior to meeting any animals. Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please). This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times. Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details. To fill out an adoption application, go to: https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Yzma is a joy. And if you are looking for a darling senior to pour your heart into, you couldn't find a more deserving girl. Found roaming in SC, Yzma was a pitiful sight. She had a poor body score and coat and she had a noticeable weakness in her rear quarters, but despite her shaking fear, there was an infinite sweetness about her.  And as soon as she left the shelter and was settled in a foster home, we were rewarded with a brilliant smile. Yzma is happy and loving and does best when she can follow the lead of a confident canine companion. She is house trained and does well without being crated.  She likes to spend her time rotating between the dog beds and exploring the yard. And she is always up for a treat or a pet. She absolutely loves snow. 

Yzma has degenerative disc disease and our vet does not feel she is a candidate for surgery. This means she will need an owner who is committed to managing her condition with a combination of oral medication and other therapies, which may include things like laser, acupuncture, etc. Other considerations like managing her weight, and restriction of high impact activity ( avoiding stair use,  not allowing her to jump on or off furniture) would be important for Yzma as well as quality food and supplements. Being that her condition is both chronic and there is the possibility of acute flare-ups, it is important for an adopter to know that this will be an ongoing process. 

We realize that Yzma's needs won't be the right match for every applicant, but this is a truly special girl in more ways than one and we do believe that there could be a special someone out there who will see that the love and devotion they give to Yzma will be returned tenfold. She's totally worth the effort. For more info or to apply, email opundo@operationunderdog.org

animal.description:
Meet Harper, a sweet little pea of a pittie with a stunning reddish brown coat and precious face to match. Harper is 2 years old and a petite girl at only 35lbs. She is very people focused and wants nothing more then a family of her own. This sensitive girl is looking for a patient adopter who will give her some time to settle into her new home and with meeting new people. Harper craves strong daily routine. Unknown things and environments make Harper anxious until acclimated. Harper is a quick learner and very treat motivated. She is house and crate trained, and does well on a leash when not distracted by new people or new dogs. Harper would do well with another calm older dog in the home and tends to follow their lead. In her foster home, Harper has done well with a dog savy cat but does like to chase the other cat in the home. Since Harper is fearful with new situations she is looking for a adult only home who is willing to be patient and continue working on earning Harper's trust. Once she trusts you, you have her loyalty completely and she will be your best friend. Does Harper sound like a good fit for your home. Please send in your adoption application today at www.underhoundrailroad.org

Harper is currently being fostered in North Carolina and can be transported to her adoptive home North.

animal.description: Hi there, my name is Jager! I am a sweet, gentle, and extremely affectionate boy. I will never pass up the chance to cuddle or spoon. I am highly intelligent and have an incredible memory. I am eager to learn and to please my human. I know some basic commands like sit, down, stay, wait and come. I am trained to sit patiently while my food is being prepared or while you are in the kitchen. My favorite toys are the squeaky ones. I show little interest in balls or ropes, but go 'nuts' for a squeaky toy. They come in handy when you want me to do something. I have mild anxiety when in the car so it's a good idea to always make sure I have one or two toys for the ride. If it is a longer drive, my foster mom gives me a bully stick and I do well. There are some manners that I am still working on such as not counter surfing for human food. I can be dog reactive on walks, but I am working on this and have progressed quite a bit. The staff and trainer here at the shelter will show my adopter how to work on this so I can continue making progress. I am selective about other dogs, some dogs I do very well with and some dogs just rub me the wrong way. I do not care for cats. I am looking for a home where I will be treated just like a member of the family! I am going to need daily exercise, training, continued socialization, and plenty of affection. My adoption fee includes my neuter, a microchip, vaccines, and a fourteen day limited health guarantee through Redstone Animal Hospital! Come visit me today! Primary Color: Black Secondary Color: White Weight: 54lbs Age: 3yrs 6mths 3wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
Emily is a sassy bundle of sunshine who likes long walks and a good cuddle with her people. Our educated guess is that she is a Pointer mix, approximately 35-40 pounds.

Emily enjoys long walks on the beach, in open fields, and in the forest. She is most comfortable hiking on the trail with my family. Smells on the trail are her favorite! I

love kids of all ages and other dogs too. Emily would like to be in a house with another dog who is my bestie and could show me the ropes. She ignores cats. Emily enjoys the dog park a lot and like to play with dogs my size or larger. She's become a greeter at the dog park and is very sociable and

always ready for a milk bone or bully stick!

This girl is looking forward to being your best friend-she's all ears and ready to hear about your day. She may not have much advice to offer, but dog cuddles and kisses are a pretty good alternative.

WHAT'S NEXT?

Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you guys to meet! It'll be kind of like a blind date!

BY APPOINTMENT ONLY:  Meetings at our Adoption Center are by appointment only (no walk-ins).  An online adoption application is required and must be approved prior to meeting any animals.  Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please).  This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times.  

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details.

https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Hi, I’m Ruby! I am a super loving retriever mix. I have enjoyed living in my foster home with some doggie friends... they are so fun to play with! When I’m not playing, I love to either chew my bones or snuggle up and nap. I am doing great with potty training and basic commands, too!

Ruby and her five sisters were surrendered to an overcrowded shelter in northern Louisiana. We believe they are golden retriever mixes who were born in September 2020. Ruby is currently around 20 lbs and is expected to be in the medium to large size range when full grown. Ruby is good with other dogs and kids (we’re not sure about cats, but expect she would be just fine with them). 

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Meet Mr. Byll a 1.5 year old 40 lb cattle dog mix. His previous foster mom claims that Byll's previous owners had to move and couldn't take him with. During that time he lived as an outside dog. His foster mom stated that he is smart because he mastered house training without a hitch! He is great with other dogs and loves to run around the yard. He is very charming, cute and the perfect size. Byll loves people and kids as well. He was very gentle with a 3 year old and a 1 month old that was in the household. He has learned to relax when he is instructed to do so. Contact us if you feel Byll could be a good match for you.

The adoption fee is $300 and covers age appropriate vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter.

 Applications are typically worked in time stamp order based on date/time of submission. If you have other dogs in your home, they must all meet the potential adoptee. It may save you a trip to bring them with you when you visit, if you are certain you want to adopt a new family member. 

*****We are currently operating by appointment only during the social distancing stage of quarantine. If you want to meet this pet, or are interested in adopting, please submit an inquiry or email to email@townandcountryhumanesociety.org.

Someone from the rescue will contact you and/or your family and determine, on a broad level, whether you might be a fit for the animal. If so, they will provide instructions for completing the application. Your application will be reviewed and you will be contacted to set up a time to meet at the shelter or the foster home. The introduction between you and the pet will be supervised by one of the dog counselors or the foster. If all goes well, you can adopt during the same visit.

Please be sure to follow us on Facebook to learn more about Town and Country Humane Society and our mission.

Blanche is the sweetest love bug! She loves all dogs/cats/people. Blanche is a 3 year old 75 lb American Bulldog Mix. Her previous foster states:

Things that need work: She is mouthy, nibbles on your hands when excited and can nibble quite hard sometimes. Never out of aggression only out of excitement. She can be overbearing with love love. She loves to get up in your face and try to sit on your lap and lick your face. Which is great if she wasnt 75 pounds! She likes to show affection by licking...a lot! Shell lick your face, hands, arms, legs even with your jeans on she licks your jeans. Can be destructive if left unattended if shes bored. Not usually a problem if you give her plenty of toys and appropriate bones to chew on. 

Things to love about Blanche!: She gets along with all dogs, cats, horses, cows, all people. Maybe too overbearing for small kids and accidentally knock them down. She sticks around very close to you outside off leash and sometimes even tries to walk between your legs. Loves to play with other dogs and helps to make shy, insecure dogs feel more relaxed with her nonchalant, playful demeanor. Completely potty trained. Crate trained although shes not a fan and will spend the first 5 to 10 minutes whining and testing the gate to see if she can get out of it.

animal.description:
Ritz is a 3 yr old 55 lb German Shepherd/Akita mix. Ritz is awesome! He is dog friendly, cat friendly, all people friendly. We have not had him around small children only because my kids are all grown up and havent had any small friends over. I believe he would do great with small kids also. 

Things that need work: He gets too excited when he meets new people and jumps up and is overbearing. Once hes been around them for a little bit he calms right down and listens and uses his manners again. He does pull hard on a leash. Hes independent and will wander off a bit on adventures and has selective hearing when called back. But he stays close and sticks around our 5 acres really well. Can be grouchy/resource guard with other dogs when food is involved. Especially around his own bowl/kennel. 

Things to love about Ritz: Loves to play with toys/balls with people and other dogs. Doesnt guard toys, will offer toys to doggie friends to play tug o war with him. If you say mine he will drop the toy in your hand. Loves to play fetch with a ball! Very smart, independent thinker. He knows sit, shake, speak, and lay down although he doesnt lay down on command good at all. Completely house trained. Crate trained, will open the door with his paw or nose to go in and lay down. Not destructive when left alone uncrated. Loves to lay at the foot of the bed and sleep like a log at night. Loves to lay close and snuggle while you scratch his chest. 

 Ritz makes awesome Chewbacca noises and talks a lot. In the mornings when he wakes up, hell stretch and make a loud Chewbacca noise like hes rolling his Rs with his tongue. He growl/talks when he is playing or when he wants attention or needs to go outside. It can sound aggressive when hes playing but hes only talking.

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

This bright eyed boy sure looks like a puppy but Rowdy is all grown up at 3 1/2 years old.  Rowdy has tested heartworm positive but there are less expensive options available which we’d be happy to discuss with you.  This happy guy weighs right about 47 pounds and his adoption fee is $200.


All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

We would ideally like someone who has had this breed before but that is not required, but at the very least someone who has had and handled a large breed dog, as he can pull and jump up, etc. 

We do recommend that any applicants research the breed, though. Dalmatians are known for being active, not hyper, but active in that they enjoy exercise and space! So we do not think an apartment placement is going to be the best for this guy.

If you are interested in Pongo, please apply today!

please contact Canine Rescue by emailing your information to: caninerescue1@gmail.com or her foster mom, Barbie at email: barbieyonce@aol.com.

WHAT MUST I DO TO ADOPT?
Complete application found at: www.caninerescue1.org.

DO YOU ADOPT OUT OF STATE?
Yes, when it is the best home for the dog. Transportation arrangements and costs are the responsibility of the adopter in addition to the adoption fee.

PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

This beautiful girl is 18 month old Ella, a gorgeous GSD.  Ella’s current weight is 64 pounds and her adoption fee is $250.


All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

animal.description:
Dog Name: Clyde
Suspected Breed(s): Terrier/ Chinese Crested mix
Gender: Male
Age: 5.5 years old 
Weight: 24 pounds
Personality: Energetic, Quick Learner, Playful, Funny, Protective, Smart, Trainable, Snuggler, Defensive
Observations with Dogs: Clyde is generally good with meeting other dogs off leash and is working on introductions on leash. He does well with other dogs in a home environment. 
Observations with Cats: Clyde prefers to be in a home without cats.
Observations with Kids: Clyde prefers to be in a home without children.House Training Progress: No accidents, but will have anxiety accidents when left alone.
Crate Training Progress: Unknown
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Smyth County, VA
Additional Information: Clyde is 24 pounds of love and absolute devotion. He would do best in a single family home where his family loves going on long walks. Exercise is key for this little terrier guy. A home with a fenced yard is ideal but not required. Clyde is currently in training for separation anxiety and is working on not barking while crated. Clyde also needs a home where his new family is dedicated to working on his leash reactivty through exercise and training. While he is house trained (!) he may have anxiety accidents when left alone. He should not be in a home with cats. Despite his challenges, he's a very quick learner and has great potential to be the best boy when housed in the right environment! He is ridiculously sweet, devoted, and loving. Clyde looks forward to greeting you with tail wags, hind-leg circus dog dancing, and an abdunce of cuddles when you walk in the door. He can't wait to meet his forever family! Apply today to meet Clyde!

Clyde's rescue was sponsored by Gaby Richeimer in honor of her move to Clyde & Co.
 

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon.

Apply for a CAT: www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adopt-a-city-kitty.html

Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

 

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

 

Adoption fees // Dogs - $395 (including puppies) unless noted; $200 for senior dogs // Cats - $150 (unless otherwise noted)

 

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 

Cat specific: Rabies, FVRCP, Feline Leukemia vaccines. They are tested for FIV and FeLV.

Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

 

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

 

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

animal.description: Barkley is a 1 year old 25lb mystery terrier mix who is looking for his person(s) to be experienced with dogs, dedicated, active and have a bag of never ending tennis balls. He's not going to be the right fit for most people, but he is going to be the most rewarding for one who is looking for someone special. Because he was a little complicated and super smart we enlisted the help of Instinct Training in Englewood NJ to help us decode this small fry. We're coming away with a better understanding of Barkley and he's leaving with a wealth of training under his belt. Barkley use to be reactive to all things outside, he's since learned how to take his cues from his trainer, to not overreact at everything on busy streets (maybe only at some things), he's also learned how to politely greet new people (ask him what the 'magic bowl' is), loose leash walking, and many other great foundation training skills. This is how the staff at Instinct describe Barkley: "The entire staff at Instinct ADORE Mr. Barkley! He is definitely a huge part of the Instinct family. He loves his humans SO much, always ready to tackle us with kisses. Barkley has really come quite a way since his first day here. We are all very attached to this sweet boy and can you blame us?!" Anyone who adopts Barkley will also definitely amass an album of funny dog photos too. He's got personality and smarts. Barkley will also come with 3 training lessons with an Instinct Trainer to help with his transition to home. home outside of the city, with no kids, adults only would be best. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines and microchipped. Make a commitment and a difference, apply to adopt Barkley here: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/SSRD/Dog

animal.description:
Like a warm cup of coffeeMaxwell is ready to warm your belly, start your day and keep you going day in and day outno caffeine necessary but he sure would love a house! Maxwell's House would ideally involve lots of people who love fun, games, laughs, silliness and antics in between naps and meals. Maxwell is a lab mix who is about a year or two old and has the best energy and is simply a blast to be around. Maxwell likes to play hard, zoom and romp and roll but loves to love and burrow in for some good cuddles whenever possible. He would do well in a home with another dog who enjoys playing as much as he does and would also love some peeps who are active and like to go and do. He is confident and ready to take on anything or nothing, just as long as he is with you and yours. Maxwell doesn't even need sugar, he brings it all and will be the boost your mood needs on even the dreariest day. Leash walking, sitting, stayingall jobs he would love to learn and treat getting will top of the list of all time fav things. Apply now for this yummy guy!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Alex & Andy are around 3 years old
Alex is the tan boy. He is 57 lb.
Andy is the brindle and white boy. He is 53 lb.
They can live with other dogs.
They have not been tested with cats at our shelter yet.

Alex & Andy are two happy, energetic pups who want to find a home together.

They really enjoy each other's company and seem to be bonded. They are always looking for the other if they aren't together.

They like to be outside together running around the yard and are learning how to play with toys. They play great with other dogs, too. They love to play chase and wrestle with their best dog friend, Lincoln.

They would make great adventure buddies once they have a little bit of leash training. They are active and fun but quiet indoors.

When spending time with them in their room, they want to play with you and cuddle. They will immediately jump into your lap and give affection.

They are both very motivated by treats. Andy knows how to sit, Alex is still learning!

--

Our hours: In an effort to limit the number of visitors at our shelter during this time, visitors are limited to approved applicants only.


Instructions on how to fill out our online application are on our website here: https://www.lighthouseanimalshelter.org/application-instructions

We are receiving a high number of applications at this time. Please be patient with us while we adjust to these new changes and keep in mind that our volunteers process the applications as quickly as their schedules allow.

We do not adopt on a first-come-first-serve basis, but rather by the best match between dog and family, although we will factor in the order of applications if there are equally good matches.

How you can help us process your application:
Please call all of your references (landlord, if applicable, vet(s) and personal references) before filling out an application to let them know that we will be calling. We are an all-volunteer program and volunteers often make reference calls from their cell phone. It will be a number your personal reference does not recognize. We understand most people will screen their calls from unknown numbers so please tell them to keep an eye on their voicemail and give the volunteer a call back at their earliest convenience. We may end up playing phone tag with your personal references but will reach out to you if we need further assistance in reaching them.

How we process your application:
Once we receive your application, we will check home ownership or landlord permission, personal references and vet references. We will reach out to you if we have questions during the process or if we are having trouble reaching your references either through email or phone. We will contact you when your application is fully processed to discuss how you would like to proceed with your application and to discuss dogs in our care who will be a good match for you and anyone involved in the adoption.

Our adoption fee:
Our adoption fee is $400 ($415 if paid by PayPal) which covers the costs of vetting (spay, vaccinations, heartworm testing, preventatives while in our care, deworming and microchip) and any boarding or transport fees incurred in each dog's rescue.

animal.description:
Meet ZOOEY! She is a super sweet, 6 month old mix, weighing in at approximately 25 lbs. We were told she is a mix of chihuahua and rat terrier, but only a DNA test will tell for sure,

ZOOEY is a super high-energy puppy who needs an active family who will walk her and play with her daily. She loves other dogs and she is currently being fostered in a home with 5 cats who she wants nothing more than to play with, but PLEASE NOTE: If you have a cat, it will need to be one who likes dogs and wants to play. Otherwise she will be too much for them. 

The best part about ZOOEY is that she is extremely loving and cuddly. She believes herself to be a lap dog. She's the perfect size too. Big enough to go on long hikes, but small enough to still cuddle up with you.

ZOOEY can be a bit mouthy, and like most high-energy puppies will require training. After basic obedience she would excel in agility. 
ZOOEY sleeps well in a crate and is house broken as long as you take her outside regularly.

ZOOEY is spayed, vaccinated for rabies and distemper, tested negative for heartworm and tick born illnesses, microchipped, and dewormed. If you are interested in giving ZOOEY her forever home please submit an application to adopt a dog online at passion4paws.org/adopt. She's waiting!

Alex & Andy are around 3 years old
Alex is the tan boy. He is 57 lb.
Andy is the brindle and white boy. He is 53 lb.
They can live with other dogs.
They have not been tested with cats at our shelter yet.

Alex & Andy are two happy, energetic pups who want to find a home together.

They really enjoy each other's company and seem to be bonded. They are always looking for the other if they aren't together.

They like to be outside together running around the yard and are learning how to play with toys. They play great with other dogs, too. They love to play chase and wrestle with their best dog friend, Lincoln.

They would make great adventure buddies once they have a little bit of leash training. They are active and fun but quiet indoors.

When spending time with them in their room, they want to play with you and cuddle. They will immediately jump into your lap and give affection.

They are both very motivated by treats. Andy knows how to sit, Alex is still learning!

Please apply now if you're interested in meeting our sweet friend!!

animal.description:
Meet Shelby! This girl was found as a stray the we are guessing was dumped by a hunter that though she was no longer useful. The family that found her took good care of her but realized she needed more attention than they could provide with 5 kids in their home.

Shelby is an awesome girl! She gets along well with other dogs and would do best with kids that are 13 and up. She is larger (69 lbs but could loose a few pounds). She is also house trained and can be crate too but she does not need to be. Shelby is spayed and up to date on all vaccines. She is Lyme positive, and is being treated for a second round with doxy. Shelby is just fine and does not have any Lyme symptoms but as in humans is can flare at times or go dormant. She will need an adopted that is willing and able to provide what she needs if it does ever become an issue.

12/12 Shelby visited our pawsome friends at Doggos, Dog Park and Pub, and had a great time! She loves playing with the other pups! 
1/18 Shelby is doing great in her foster home and learning better leash walking skills. She does great with the other dogs in her foster and is ok with the cat but would do best in a home with no cats! 

If you are interested in Shelby please apply at reddoffarm.com!

Meet Steve! 

He is a 1 year old Pit Bull mix who weighs about 60 pounds. Steve is a ball of energy and absolutely loves toys of all kinds! He is very shy at first, especially with men, but once he knows you he runs into your lap immediately. He is a high energy dog who loves to run and play, and shows potential to play with other dogs as well. He can be tentative with new dogs, but enjoys playing and wrestling when he gets the chance! He shows potential to live in a home with another dog if it is a good fit. Since Steve can be shy at first, if there are children in the home they would need to be ages 13 and older. Steve is shy at first with men, and may take multiple visits for him to trust you, but with the help of some delicious treats he's your new best friend! 

If Steve looks like the lovable pup that's missing from your life, give us a call at 234-212-9843 to schedule an appointment to meet him today!

Hi there! My name is Latte!

I'm a super sweet girl who is always ready for cuddles and snack time. I'm the biggest lovebug, but I can be a little shy at times, so I'm looking for a family that can help me boost my confidence and help socialize me more with potential human and doggie friends. I'm so excited for all the adventures we'll go on! I've lived in a home before so I know a thing or two about being a good roommate and know a lot of my big girl manners already. I would love for you to bring the whole family down to meet me if I sound like the pup for you!

I'm Beemer's Buddy! Thanks to Chapman BMW Camelback you can take me home for FREE!

Make an appointment to meet me at AAWL's Main Shelter!

https://aawl.org/content/appointment-based-adoptions

AAWL recommends I live with humans HIGH SCHOOL AGE and older.
AAWL says I am SOCIAL with other dogs.
AAWL says I am a WEEKEND ATHLETE, needing regular exercise.
AAWL does not know if I can live with cats at this time.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Ace (male) and Baby (female) are a bonded pair.

Imagine cuddling these 12-year-old cuties in your arms! Adorable Ace, at 10 pounds and beautiful Baby at 6 pounds will warm your hearts and your home with their sweet, winning ways. Called the "show pony" by his fosters, Ace prances around like a show horse in the yard, jumps on their laps when they're working at their desks, snuggles with them under the covers, and LOVES taking rides in the car. Shier Baby needs some time before she lets herself be picked up, then cuddling becomes her passion followed by "digging" blankets on the couch or bed. Both get along easily with the resident cats, are famously fond of treats, (Ace eats mini Milk Bone biscuits and Baby eats soft treats), appear to be deaf and have few remaining teeth. Housetrained, with the occasional accident, this precious pair hopes to find fur-ever love in a tranquil home without children that will cherish them for the cuddly cuties they are.

Animal Rescue of the Rockies believes that every pet should find a wonderful, caring home. To ensure each pet finds the best possible home, we ask that you fill out our Adoption Application so we can learn more about you and your household. We review each application we receive and will contact you within 48 hours. If your home sounds like a good match for you and the pet, the next step is to set up a "meet and greet." After meeting the pet, if you would like to proceed with adopting, we'll ask that you read and sign our Adoption Agreement and pay the adoption fee. Our adoption fees help cover the costs of saving more lives! A home visit will be scheduled within one week of your new pet going home with you.

The adoption fee for Ace and Baby is $150. Our adoption fee covers the following:

- Spay/Neuter, Microchip

- DAPP vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for all DAPP boosters after adoption.

- Rabies vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for any rabies vaccinations after adoption.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an adoption application by clicking here . We want our pets to go to a lifelong new home, so thank you for your patience during the adoption process!

Please email ARRColorado@gmail.com for more information, as we can not accept calls at this time. Our adoption process is:

1. Fill out our Adoption Application online. We'll contact you within 48 hours to answer any questions you may have about the pet.

2. If the pet looks like a great match, we'll schedule a meet and greet and ask you to fill out our online Adoption Agreement if you'd like to proceed with adopting. Once you've completed the Adoption Agreement and pay the pet's Adoption Fee, you can arrange to pick up your new furry family member!

animal.description:
Meet "Ranger.  He was found wandering the mountain trails by a wonderful family who took him in and gave him a place to stay while searching for his owners.  Ranger joined our foster program 9 months ago! He was shy and reserved at first but thanks to his finder & foster family he got a chance to change his story.  Ranger has now spent the last three months in basic training to learn to be a dog and is now ready for his forever home.  

Ranger will need ongoing confidence boosting and training. He is still shy but is worlds better than when he came to us. His trainer says his ideal home would be a single woman or a chill couple. He tends to gravitate more towards women. Ideally due to his shyness, a home without young children is best but teenagers would be fine.  This home would also be quiet but still up for taking him out to play, for walks and continuing his socialization. Ranger has done well with another dog previously, but has not spent a lot of time with other dogs since his training. The dogs he has met though, he has been friendly with! Ranger is crate trained and it is really important that his adoptive home keep up with crating him as it is his safe space. 

He loves playing in his fosters fenced yard, but wants to be with his people. He does not like storms or loud noises but has gotten better with that over the time he's been with us. Ranger LOVES toys but will destroy them. He either needs supervised toy time or harder toys that he can't rip up and eat. He has been neutered, microchipped and is current on vaccines. Ranger is a great boy who has been given a second chance at a great life! If you are interested in giving this boy a forever home, please apply at reddogfarm.com!

animal.description:
Duke is a sweet, affectionate and extremely handsome 52 lb 8.5 year old gentleman! He has been in NEESSR foster care for a little over a month now, so we’ve learned quite a bit about him. Duke loves his 3 mile daily walks and he LOVES attention from his people. His foster mom reports he also LOVES car rides, his stuffed toys and belly rubs.  His favorite treat is a large knuckle bone filled with peanut butter – keeps him busy for hours.  He does NOT like to share his home with other dogs and he does NOT like to be left alone! Duke has a history of skin & allergy issues which are now controlled by a strict diet including prescription dog food and the use of allergy medication. We are looking for an active adopter who can provide Duke much love and exercise.

PLEASE NOTE –  REQUIREMENTS FOR ADOPTING DUKE: 
***He MUST be the only dog in the home. If you have doggy visitors or need to board your dog in a facility or home with other dogs, he is not the dog for you.
*** He MUST be kept on the prescription dog food and allergy meds.
*** His adopter MUST be home a great deal of the time. Adopter should be retired or work-from-home permanently

If you already are on our adoption waiting list and are interested in learning more about Duke please email neessr@gmail.com.  Otherwise please read about our adoption policies and then complete our application.  https://essrescue.org/adoptionprocess.html

NEESSR adopters must live in New England or New York state and we do not accept applicants with children under the age of 5.

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

Little Miss Lola is an adorable 10 month old Shar Pei mix youngster.  Puppies are puppies and crate training is the best way to raise a young one.  Lola’s current weight is about 20 pounds and her adoption fee is $200.


All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

Adoption fee for this dog will be $150.00, which helps with the expenses for spaying or neutering your pet, all vaccinations, including rabies up to date, microchip, and any other grooming or medical care that was needed when the dog was rescued by ARF. 

Due to the high demand for puppies/dogs we anticipate multiple applications on any of our dogs/puppies. We will review each submitted application, then contact the approved adopter via email. If that particular person has changed their mind we will move to the next approved adopter. Thank you for understanding. If you are interested please complete an application at www.arf-fresno.com   

Cassie a 13 yr old senior has lost her owners due to COVID.  She is really a good girl weighing 11 lbs.   She rides well in the car and is good with big or small kids.   Cassie is friendly. She is house trained and crate trained.  However she will need to learn a new routine so she may have accidents in your house.    She likes baths. She does not like to be squeezed too hard.    She understands the words, come, sit no, stay and down.    She likes to go on walks. She is a little hesitant with women, but ultimately is okay.    She is sweet and cuddly.   We just had her teeth done ( dental). She lost 14 teeth but she is now hoping somebody will adopt her and allow her to live the rest of her life ina warm cozy bed in her with her family.  


If you would like to fill out an application online, you can go to our website at www.arf-fresno.com, click on the Adoption Section and complete the application.

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

This bright eyed boy is 3 1/2 year old Cooper.  He’s an Aussie mix and prone to be a bit of an escape artist so we’ve been told so a secure yard or leash walk would be required.  Cooper has tested heartworm positive but there are less expensive options available which we’d be happy to discuss with you.   Cooper only weighs about 29 pounds.  His adoption fee is $200.

All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

animal.description:
Hi there, Im Red! Im a lovely soul. Because, no matter what Ive been through in my life, Im happy and content in the here and now. I just want to play and have fun and enjoy every single minute of every single day that were together. My smile and my spirit will help brighten your day and your life too, if you just give me a chance.
Im an adorable, 6-year-old, 83-pound sweetheart with a beautiful smile and a truly delightful personality. And I think I must be at least partially housebroken, because I keep my kennel clean and I know to go to the bathroom when I get outside. Please stay patient with me when we get home though and remember that Im trying my best to follow all the rules of my new home. I came to Wayside as a transfer from a shelter in New Orleans when they didnt have room for me. Lucky for me, I never, ever have a bad day, so I took the trip in stride. Youll notice I have a few scars left over from my previous life, including on my left eye, but none of that bothers me a bit. Im all about the fun, celebrating the day, and living each new day to the fullest.
Ive been at the shelter for awhile now, so I recently enrolled in a training program. Its so much fun! Im learning basic commands and manners in a positive, focused way. I love the extra time and attention I get from my training partner! Im one smart cookie and I pick up on things quickly. I hope you will continue to train me throughout my life. And please stay patient and calm with me as I learn what you expect from me.
Im loose and friendly and relaxed and calm when meeting new people. I love to be by your side! When one of my favorite volunteers stops by to visit me, I greet her with my favorite ball. We go out to the play yard, where I carefully line all my balls up in preparation for a great game of fetch. Toys and balls and fetch and playing are things that bring me so much joy, its hard for me to put into words. Im pretty sure I will make you smile and laugh all day long at my silly antics. Im an expert at making you as happy as you make me. 
Everyone around Wayside talks about what a hidden gem I am. They like to spend time with me because Im an easy dog to love, in addition to my happy, fun, social, affectionate personality. I love to go for daily walks and I do well on my leash. Im a strong dog though, so I like to use a harness to keep me from pulling. After a walk and my play time, theres nothing that brings me happiness like cuddling with you on the couch. Ill make such a nice companion for you! Im looking for a home as your only dog. And I need a home with kids over the age of at least 6. I can get pretty focused on my toys and I need people in my life who can understand that.
Im just a simple dog looking for a family to share my life with. I wont ask for much and Ill be happy and grateful for all the little things that come with being part of a family. Ill show you how it feels to be loved unconditionally and Ill teach you the beauty of living and appreciating whatever the moment holds.
Love, Red
 ...

animal.description:
Gotta Love Lucy

Lucy loves people and if she could talk, that would be her direct quote. At 82 lbs, she is a big, strong Terrier mix girl, but she wears it well.  Lucy is 7 yrs old, active and fun loving and is looking for a family that is the same. She likes to go for walks, car rides play in the yard, but she also is satisfied sitting in the backyard and chilling with her friends.

Lucy would prefer to be the focus of your attention soaking up as much love as possible.  Cats are unknown and because of her size, she requires a 6 ft fenced in yard and would love to play with kids 12 years of age and up. 

She has lived a somewhat difficult and sheltered life but you wouldn't know it by her happiness. And now, Lucy is ready to make up for lost time.

If you are interested in Lucy, contact us at adoptions@suncoastanimalleague.org

animal.description:
Puppy BELLALINA is up for adoption to an experienced Eskie owner. 
She is stubborn when corrected. But she's catching on that she is not the alpha, and is treat motivated so she is learning new tricks. 
She LOVES to PLAY!  She needs a dog her size or bigger that doesn't mind her tackling them. Needs a big walker or someone that is very active.  If left alone to get bored she'll chew things up.
She turns 2 years old in May. bark.
No apartment life for her either.  She'll bark if left alone. 
No invisible fence, no doggie door, or tie out, but then no dog in our rescue will be treated in that way. It is dangerous to let your dogs outside unattended. 
Cats? No small kids, older ones with dog experience. 
Please email us at ohioeskierescue@outlook.com for an application. 
We do not adopt out our dogs to far from the rescue incase things don't work out. Our dogs always remain part of the OAER family.
We took her from the Wayne County Dog Shelter here in Ohio.

animal.description:
Sophie recently survived parvo, and she's ready to find her happily ever after. She's a shy girl who will need an understanding family to help her build her confidence, but she loves fiercely, and we just know she'll make someone very happy. She is only 7 months old so she is a blank slate ready to learn how to be a good girl. 

While she technically can still be shedding this virus for another 4 weeks, we feel as though she is healthy enough to find her new family. We will require that any currently owned dogs be up to date on vaccinations if you’re thinking of adopting. This girl has been cooped up for weeks during her quarantine and treatment so she will need a family that is willing to give her time to adjust to being a regular pup. However, we would recommend not taking her out into any public setting for the next few months, disposing of any poop immediately, and not bringing another un-vaccinated dog into your home for up to 2 years.

animal.description:
Anye is a 5 year old girl that comes to us all the way from China. Her life has been beyond turbulent. She was a breeding machine at first and once she was no longer in desirable age she was destined for the meat market. Everything changed for her when an amazing rescue in China saved her life and started working with American rescues to get her out. She was one of the 21 pugs brought over by PugHearts in early January of 2021.

Despite her rough life her spirit is not broken in the slightest. She loves toys, other dogs but above all her humans. We call her happy bunny because she has the softest fur I have ever felt and she just hops around happily all day. Because this is her first experience of ever being in a house we are working on potty training but to our absolute delight she loves her crate and never has an accident in it.

As far as her health is concerned, she came to us with a UTI and some fold dermatitis but both are resolving nicely. She does have dry eyes and will need drops for life. She has some mild vision impairment but gets around just fine. Her paws are deformed forever from living in a crate with no bottom so they appear swollen all the time, not that it stops her from hopping. She does have luxating patellas in both her back legs so she is a bit bow legged, it honestly just adds to her charm. She will need her nares and soft palate corrected which is scheduled for February 16th. Once that is completed, this girl is ready for the one last move, to a home that will love her until the end of her days.

Whoever ends up with this sunshine of a girl will have something truly special. Until then we will love on her a little extra to try to make up for what she's been through.

animal.description:
** Due to breed restrictions, I cannot be adopted out to a home in Louisville or Lone Tree **
** Experienced Owners Only **
** Potential Adopters must become temporary volunteers in order to work with be before adopting **

What's cookin good lookin? My name is Cypress and I am a 2 year old German Shorthair mix. I made my way to MaxFund as a stray with my brother. My start here was rough as I had a hard time getting comfortable with my new surroundings. At first, I was having a hard time trusting people and would often get nervous and scared. As a good boy in training I've been working on trusting people and other dogs. With the help of my trainer and brother I have gotten much more comfortable with everything. My brother found his forever home and now I am ready to find mine!

Due to my prior nervousness my potential owners will need to schedule time to meet me multiple times before I can go home. I will need to learn to get comfortable with my new family. I will need to continue with my training in order to become a top notch canine citizen. I can not go to a home with children who are under 16 years old.
I am a very smart boy and even know how to sit. I like to play fetch, be outside, and most importantly goof around. Tennis balls are my favorite but I'm not picky when it comes to my toy time!

Any potential adopters must become temporary volunteers just to volunteer with me.

Are you sold yet? If you still need me to convince you, come on down to the dog shelter and let my smile charm you in person! Please call the dog shelter at 303.595.4917 to make an appointment.


MaxFund is a physical shelter located at 1005 Galapago St in Denver, Colorado.
If you are interested in learning more about a dog, please call 303-595-4917 or come into the dog shelter.
This PetFinder account is managed by volunteers, and the most up-to-date information is at the shelter.
How our adoption process works:
1. You MUST come into the shelter to meet a dog you are interested in (and meet a few others, while you’re at it!)
                We do not require appointments – come anytime during normal business hours.
                Our hours are 10-5 Mon, Wed, Thu Fri / 11-5 Saturday / 12-5 Sunday
                We suggest you call ahead to be sure the dog(s) do not have pending applications
2. You will fill out your adoption application, including references, after finding a dog you’d like to adopt
3. The application review and reference checks will take up to 3-5 business days; you will not be able to bring a dog home same-day
                We only take 2 applications per dog, before they are unavailable. This is why we suggest you call ahead to check the status of the pup!
 
We do not adopt out-of-state.
Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
Heidi was originally found in a homeless encampment at Venice Beach.   She was rescued from there and brought into a home who has just realized he is not equipped for a puppy.   So onward and upward.  New foster home, more training!

Heidi is extremely social, plays nicely with all other dogs and loves her humans.   She loves fetch, zoomies, car rides and water.    She is not fond of her crate and is learning how to behave on leash.    She is so smart….huge improvement over the last week.    And she likes discipline and routine.   It gets her brain working.

Lab puppies are lots of work.   They are high energy and need exercise and walks.    Heidi is no exception.    She needs an adopter who is committed to keeping her active, happy and continuing her training.    They may be a lot of work but they thrive on learning and training.

Think about it.   Don’t just go on her gorgeous looks.    If you are up for the task, Heidi is ready to give you lots of love and good times!

animal.description:
ELVIS
Chihuahua / Dachshund Mix
(DOB: 11/01/19)

At just 13 pounds, this little Chiweenie will win your heart!  He is the best of both worlds; able to play on his own, or be your cuddly lap dog. Elvis is super cute with eyebrows full of expressions!

He loves to play with his toys but he’ll keep a watchful eye for when you sit down, then he’s in full cuddle mode!  His favorite place is snuggled into your arm; he’ll give you kisses and fall blissfully asleep.

Elvis doesn’t react too strongly to anything, except abrupt movements, which do startle him.  He may react with a little squeal, but nothing more.  He is also learning to share his toys – he has never had them before so his furry foster brother is showing him the ropes on sharing.  He has a great appetite and patiently waits for his foster siblings to finish eating before going to lick their bowls.  He is house-trained and crate-trained. 
 
Elvis is up-to-date on vaccines, neutered, microchipped and being maintained on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention.  

This dog is currently being fostered as part of Diamonds in the Ruff Canine Rescue. An application is required, along with a home visit and small adoption fee.  Applicants must be at least 21 years of age. **FENCED IN YARD REQUIRED**

Please visit us on our Facebook page for additional photos, give us a like while you're there! 
https://www.facebook.com/diamondsintheruffNC

All of our dogs are fostered in homes and are INDOOR dogs. We believe all dogs are family members and should be treated as valued members of the household. 

Please review our adoption guidelines for further information on adopting from Diamonds in the Ruff Canine Rescue before submitting an application. www.DITRnc.com.

IN VERMONT

Meet Puddin! Here is her video in NC:

https://youtu.be/ivBMYp0zZdA

Puddin is 10 years old (approx. DOB 12-10-10), female, 38 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed, and micro-chipped. This poor girl was found abandoned and homeless in NC in rough shape. She was out of time and we could not bare the thought of this sweet soul losing her life unloved in an overcrowded shelter! We saved her! She has had full vetting including removing numerous "surface" masses after our Vet said the surgery was safe and recommended (not sent to lab). Puddin tested well with other dogs offering soft tail wags. Although she is a bit hard of hearing and her sight is not 20/20 she loves to explore and seems very grateful to have been saved. Puddin is looking for her happily ever after............finally. Is that with your family? Stay tuned for more information as Puddin is a new rescue!

If you are interested in adopting Puddin please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

Are you looking for the BEST dog ever who has a couple special needs... but SHHHHHHH... do not tell Ranger that!
Ranger the 2 year old Beabull is on the search for his forever home. Ranger is full of energy with an addiction to toys, the louder the better. He has requested that his special family be able to supply him with lots of fun toys to keep him busy and happy. He will need a fenced yard, a family that is home more than not, a kid to play with would be a plus, another dog with similar energy who will allow him to be the toy hog or he would do fine as an only, a family that will allow him to sleep in bed with them and hangout on the furniture. Ranger loves walks, he is super fast, has zero street smarts and fears nothing going by so a harness and a strong handler would be best. Ranger has done phenomenal recovering from surgery after being hit by a vehicle but does have some needs as a result. He can not urinate when he tries but wears a belly band and urine releases when he barks, sits or lays down. He has zero issues with wearing his fancy pants. Ranger also has trouble when pooping, it takes him time and on occasion releases on its own when he barks. He will need his family to be understanding of his special needs. Ranger is a happy dog who loves to give kisses and be near his humans, he will truly be a great addition to the perfect home. Applications are available on our website

animal.description:
*TO APPLY GO TO www.LuckyDogRefuge.com*

Meet Halo, our miracle girl! She was found blind and emaciated in the woods in MS when one of our fosters rescued her. Since then, she has gained plenty of weight and rehabilitated beautifully! 

Despite what she has been through, she is a very gentle soul with a heart of gold. She absolutely adores people and attention - she can't get enough! She is sweet, gentle, and despite having only a few teeth, she loves treats. She would love a home where she can hang out with her people and live the good life. 

At the refuge, she has her own room and is able to stay free in it, instead of being crated. She is a chill girl in her room and doesn't make a mess! 

She is fully blind but adapts amazingly to her environment. At her foster, she navigates the steps, which took her just a couple days (and a few meatballs)  to learn. She boogies around the yard and her foster tells her “uh uh uh" when she gets near a tree.  She leaps in a car perfectly and follows her person around the yard by the sound of their footsteps. She adapts so well, you'd even find yourself questioning if she really is indeed blind (she is).

She is getting her heartworm treatment - which is covered by the rescue - and will be spayed afterwards. She has a cyst on her ovary that will be removed with the spay. 

This sweet girl is an absolute gem! She knows she is a star and is so happy to be living her best life now. Little does she know it is about to get even better! Apply now at www.LuckyDogRefuge.com 

READ THE FOLLOWING FOR INSTRUCTIONS ON SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION FOR THIS PET:

- The first step towards adoption is to complete an adoption application, which can be found online at our website www.LuckyDogRefuge.com, under the “Apply Now” tab 

or 

at https://forms.gle/LXKMKSnagxLSad668.

- Do NOT use the Petfinder links or email to ask us about our adoptable dog listings - we do not always receive these messages and will not respond to them.

- Please do not ask if a dog is still available - we do our best to update their status as quickly as possible. If a dog is listed for adoption, it means we have not yet approved an adopter and are still accepting applications.

- PLEASE NOTE THAT ONLY APPROVED ADOPTERS WILL BE PERMITTED TO MEET OUR RESCUES.

Thanks for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description:
Please read the entire write up, prior to inquiring or completing an application.  
Thank you!

Adoption Requirements:
- Must have fenced yard
- Must have another playful dog
- Must live within 60 minutes travel of Hatfield PA

Shadow is 3-1/2 years old and about 60 lbs.  He is a nervous dog that will need time to settle in a new home.  Shadow received little to no socialization prior to coming into rescue.  He will likely always be anxious in new situations or around new people.  Shadow does love other dogs and is good with cats.  He has a medium energy level and will need daily exercise along with regular grooming.

If you can provide Shadow a home with another playful dog, a fully fenced in yard, willingness to use a crate, a quiet house, and lots of patience, please request the application, complete and return via email to: suehm2312@gmail.com Or ruffcollies@outlook.com
Previous experience with herding dogs would be a plus.

The process includes: 
- interested party submits the completed application , (see email info above)
- rescue reviews the application 
- references checked
- visit scheduled for you, your family and all current dogs to meet Shadow at a Souderton, PA foster home.  

All visits will be conducted during daylight hours outside in a fenced in yard.  Prior to finalizing the adoption, a home visit will be required by a collie rescue volunteer to the home of the prospective adopter. We are requesting that prospective adopters be within a 60-minute travel distance of Souderton, PA.

Adoption fee is $300.

Thank you!!

IN NEED OF LOCAL FOSTER OR ADOPTER/ AVAILABLE FOR FOSTER TO ADOPT FOR LOCAL ADOPTERS

Meet Carson! Here is his video in NC:

https://youtu.be/_89NWbvNc7c

Carson is 2 years old (approx. DOB tbd), male, 48 lbs., vetted, is or will be neutered, and micro-chipped. Carson was found as a homeless stray in North Carolina with embedded collar scars on the underside of his neck. We don't think Carson was ever truly loved; he is so loves attention and seeks affection! He is very friendly with other dogs and assessed well during introductions. He is an energetic happy boy that would love a family of his own! He is jumpy currently so probably best older children. Stay tuned for more information as Carson is a new rescue!

If you are interested in fostering or adopting Carson please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out his Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description:
We're Dani's puppies and ready to find our forever families. We were born on 11/6/2020. Our mom, Dani, appears to be a rat terrier mix, but we do not know the daddies' breed. Based on the way some of us look, we think possibly a Doxie/mix. We think we will be smaller dogs, as mom is 12-13 pounds and we weight 4 to 8 pounds now. The 2 boys, Berlin and Dublin, are bigger than the girls. 
Although we are "puppylicious" and cuteness overload, make no mistake about it-WE ARE A LOT OF WORK! We are like infants without diapers. We have sharp teeth and nails, and sometimes can unintentionally scratch you. We eat puppy kibble 3-4 times a day and need access to water all day. We do our best to use our puppy pads, but sometimes we forget. We tear apart our toys and anything we think may be a toy! We will need to be socialized, housebroken, obedience trained, leash trained, cuddled, kept safe and loved, so we can become wonderful family members. We will go through a teething process and when the time is right we are required by AHF to get spayed/neutered. Our mom, Dani, was lucky and through wonderful rescues found a foster home to have her babies in a safe, comfortable environment. Others, with unplanned pregnancies, are not as fortunate.
. We will be better family members if we also go to some training after we get all our vaccinations. Since we are small dogs we would do better with families without young, little children. Older children and people over 21 are OK. We would do OK in a condo/apartment or a home. If the adopters are renting or have an HOA, the document will need to be available at the time of adoption to make sure we meet their pet requirements. AHF also requires adopters use a Martingale collar, and because we are small a harness-double leashing, so we can't accidently escape and get away. We should never be left unattended outside as our mom, Dani, is quite a good jumper, as a rat terrier may also be a digger, and because of the local wildlife and larger birds (hawks and eagles). AHF also requires a home visit prior to adoption and a meet/greet with other animals in the family. We have never met a cat. 
If you are interested, please fill out and submit an application. Only qualified applicants will be considered. Due to Covid guidelines, we will initially conduct phone interviews and then schedule a home visit/meet and greet. Once it's a match, the adopters will need to go to the PetCo in Bloomingdale on Army Trail Road, Saturday between 11 and 2 to sign the paperwork with an Adoption Counselor. 
The adoption fee is $475 which includes deworming, microchipping, 3 sets of puppy shots, rabies and neuter when old enough. After his/her neuter, you will get a $55 refund.
Email: puppies@almosthomefoundation.org
Almost Home Foundation's adoption requirements:
(1) Be at least 21 years of age;
(2) Have the consent of all adults living in the household;
(3) Have approval from the residence owner;
(4) Have valid ID with current address;
(5) Be approved by Almost Home Foundation as a suitable adoptive home; and
(6) Live in the suburbs surrounding Schaumburg (Illinois Residents only)
*** Please note that Almost Home Foundation accepts only cash or checks for adoption fees; we do not accept debit or credit cards. ***

animal.description:
Love for Life Program:

The dog you are interested in is eligible for our Love for Life program (L4L).  This program is to find forever foster homes for dogs that may not otherwise find a forever home.  Many are more difficult for adoption due to medical or behavioral conditions.  You can read more about our Love for Life program on our website at http://www.savingpawsrescueaz.com/love-for-life-program/.

Please meet the newest member of our Love For Life Program~
Temperance (Tempe) came to us as a stray that wondered onto someone's property in Tucson and that person reached out to a friend that knew about our rescue. He reached out to us after holding onto her for a couple of days then drove her to our rescue from Tucson.  This middle-aged girl was so skinny and weak, but also had a very bloated belly. Within a couple of hours we had her into the vet that informed us her belly was full of rocks, trash, bones, and even Christmas tree ornament hooks! This poor girl was so hungry she was eating anything she could find.  

So the path of getting this girl healthy started. With the help of all the volunteers at the rescue, she slowly started to get better. As time went on, we found out she is diabetic, which now means small amounts of insulin twice a day along with a controlled diet.  With the diabetes, Tempe started losing her eye sight, which sadly resulted in having to have one of her eyes removed. We believe she can slightly see shadows with the other eye. 

With all of that going on with this special girl, it does not stop her from having fun. She loves toys... especially balls.  She loves to go on walks and is just all around a happy girl. She loves to be with her person, so we think someone home a lot would be best for her. Because of her limited eyesight, we're not sure how she would do around other dogs, so she would probably be happiest as an only dog.

We are looking for a Love For Life foster home for Tempe.  As a foster, all necessary supplies and food would be provided for you by the rescue.  Tempe deserves to spend the rest of her days in a home of her own, with people of her own to love.  Are you that person?

If you think you could give this precious girl a soft place to land, please fill out the foster application below:
http://www.savingpawsrescueaz.org/foster/

We will only schedule meet and greets with an approved application. We are an all-volunteer organization. We are not compensated for our time. Many volunteers juggle family and full -time careers while volunteering at Saving Paws. It may take up to 5 days to process an application and complete reference checks.

Thank you for your interest in saving the life of a dog.

animal.description:
Hi there!  Thanks for stopping by.  I know that the paperwork says I am a 30 lb, 4 month old, bulldog mix, but in truth, I am actually 100% wigglebutt.  I love people and am wiggling right now just thinking that my forever family is reading this. I don’t exactly have the greatest past, but I know I can have the best future with you.

While in foster care, I have learned quite a bit about living in a home.  I am getting pretty good at potty training - and if you have some patience, a schedule, and some hot dogs, you shouldn’t expect many accidents!  I do a great job, once I know where I am supposed to go.  I am learning to walk on a leash and don’t really pull at all.  I just want to be beside you while walking.  My foster parents say I am the brave one - and I like to explore new things.  I haven’t had issues with chewing things I am not supposed to, but foster mom keeps everything picked up.  At night I sleep in a crate without issues.  I did have one night separate from my brother and I cried a bit, but when my foster sister went into the crate adjacent to mine, I was just fine.  

In foster care, I have lived with my brother, Hulk.  If you want to adopt us both, you will not be disappointed.  We play together well and he makes the best wrestling partner.  If we go to separate homes, that is okay too.  I have not had issues with other dogs and am getting along fairly well with cats.  They sort of ignore me and I am confused by them - so no issues!  

I look forward to a lifetime of adventures and cuddles with you and promise to nuzzle you and be by your side in good times and bad!

animal.description: Cheerio is almost 4 months old, and from early on, she struggled with *ahem* bathroom issues. Due to a possible genetic defect (most likely) to an untreated parasitic infection (probably a lending factor) she had a prolapsed rectum that neither medications, nor surgery could repair. (We tried) These days, her bum is mostly in place. The major concern of infection is gone, and for the most part she LOOKS normal. But sadly, she was left with a rather severe and particularly unpleasant lasting effect. She is completely incontinent. She cannot hold her urine, or feces, and must be diapered, unless of course outside, or confined to an area where her uncontrolled bladder and bowel movements are not an issue. I repeat- ignore cute Boston puppy face and read- SHE MUST BE DIAPERED. Forever.
